<br>
Question: can you give a general idea of how physically far these numbers are?  That is, 125, 50, and 20.  I have no point of reference and I haven't taken the time to learn the coordinate system in this game (landmarks work extremely well).  I could log in and check but you probably know off the top of your head.<br>
<br>
Also, pointing something out because I think a few people missed it:<br>
<br>
The distance non-detect sees a person at versus a detect person, with...<br>
<br>
...1 level higher than stealth skill of hider, 145 vs 175<br>
...2 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 165 vs 225<br>
...5 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 225 vs 375<br>
...10 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 325 vs 625<br>
...20 levels higher than stealth skill of hider, 525 vs 1125<br>
<br>
No opinion on that, just pointing it out.  We don't see stealthed people 2.5x as far away as someone without detect hidden; it starts even, and gets exponentially more, working out to near 2x as the disparity increases.  If our minimum chance were doubled (to 250), it would start at double and go up from there, instead of starting even and approaching double.  Nevermind, I have an opinion: the latter is definitely how it should be.<br>
<br>
Also, afterthought: it kinda seems like Stealth was balanced for archers (who stay at a range at all times if they can) rather than assassins (who purposely put themselves in melee range). <p><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valarauco.gif"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A> at: 2/1/02 4:00:00 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usquinkmcpoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Squink McPoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 4:58:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> I meant to include a point of reference so that '125' means something, but my notes are missing it.<br>
