<br>
Simple fix (for detection purposes only):<br>
<br>
if seeker has detect hidden<br>
((target's_stealth*(target's_stealth/target's_level)) - seeker's_stealth*(seeker's_stealth/seeker's_level).<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = effective Stealth level of target.<br>
<br>
Some examples:<br>
<br>
level 20 seeker 20 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:  <br>
(30 - 16) = target has 14 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively slightly less than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br>
<br>
level 20 seeker 20 stealth          level 40 target with 40 stealth:<br>
<br>
(40 - 16) = target has 24 levels of stealth at level 40, or effectively slightly more than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br>
<br>
level 30 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:<br>
(30 - 24) = target has 6 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively 20% specc'd in Stealth.<br>
<br>
level 40 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 30 stealth:<br>
<br>
(30 - 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = target has 12 levels of stealth at level 30, or effectively slightly less than half-specc'd in Stealth.<br>
<br>
level 40 seeker 30 stealth          level 30 target with 20 stealth:<br>
<br>
(13 - 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  = target has 0 levels of stealth at 30, or effectively no spec points in Stealth.<br>
<br>
level 40 seeker 40 stealth          level 40 target with 40 stealth:<br>
<br>
(40 - 32) = target has 8 levels of stealth at level 40, or effectivelyl 20% spec in Stealth.<br>
<br>
<br>
Couple things this system would do.  It would only be used for detection by classes which possessed Detect Hidden.  It would depend on the Stealth of the seeker *and* the target.  It would not be solely character-level based.  With both seeker and target full-specc'd, it would effectively lead to the target being 20% specc'd in Stealth at any given level.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Trenos <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usmudgedaemelar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Smudge DaeMelar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://cwmonkey.virtualave.net/s/net8/laghost.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:48:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1991.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 50 vs lower</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> For characters that are the same level or lower than the stealth level of the person hiding, there is no advantage to having detect hidden. The minimum detection radius is the same for all characters in this situation. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
