<br>
Ok we got something to work with...<br>
the only bother I have so far is that what we have ta work with SEEMS to have us picking on lower con. <br>
<br>
Inagine a RvR melee, at approx 3 horse lengthas away are stealthed Yellow Con, High Blue Con, Low Green Con. <br>
<br>
Obviously I &quot;see the Green&quot; and go for him, not seeing the other two. This is far from what Mythic or the players want. I want a crack at that yellow con, barring that at least the blue.<br>
Someone has already stated that constant killing of lowbies will result in MORE screeching to nerf the class rather then less. <br>
<br>
I think &quot;Detect Hidden&quot; should be an Empirical Skill. S<br>
ay 2% Chance per level to detect hidden up to 100% Chance at 50th level. <br>
The Hidden One's training in stealth should LOWER this chance. But not dead even. Maybe say 1.5% per level trained. So a L50 Stealth 50 could negate 75% of the 100% leaving 25% chance to detect.<br>
Range Impact. An Archer can notch and shoot in say 3.7-4 seconds buffed with the big bow. An Assassin can run approximatly 800 of your range in that 4 seconds. Have that be the base; closer goes up, farther goes down. <br>
<br>
Max Vision is approx 2500 of yer measurements. -90%<br>
Max Archery Range is therefore 1600 -75%<br>
Average Range closing is then 1200 -50%<br>
Base Range is then 600 0<br>
Close Range is therefore 400 +10%<br>
Melee Range is usually 50-100 depending on weapon. +20%<br>
<br>
<br>
Under this formulae a Level 40/Effective Stealth 40 has a 5% chance per check to see a Stealth Skill1 at Max Range, <br>
a 10% chance to see a Stealth Skill 20 at 1200,<br>
a 20% chance to see a Stealth Skill 40 at 600,<br>
a 15% chance to see a Stealth Skill 50 at 400,<br>
a 25% Chance to see a Stealth Skill 50 at 100.<br>
<br>
These checks would be totally above and beyond the &quot;see invisible&quot; all players get Level/Stealth Level.<br>
<br>
Suggested mechanics of how to check, rather then all or nothing every 3 seconds; work the Square of the chance to see 8/10th second. So you would have a 4% chance every 8/10th second to detect (Mathmatically same % in 3 seconds just more frequent checks). This allows running characters to uncover archers, Rather than run-stop-count 3-run-stop-count 3. <br>
<br>
Now, How to transfer data that fast?... have the CODE for the hidden Stealther transfer constantly but not display on monitor until a Detect Stealthed check is passed. Then the next monitor refresh (I think its 75 times a second now) there they are. <br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
And again, Huff, THANKS for all you've accomplished and done so far already.<br>
<br>
Jammer of Hibernia/Palomides<br>
